## Data Attribution

This software integrates and references data from the following sources,
each governed by their own terms:

- **Sentinel-1 / Sentinel-2**: © European Space Agency (ESA), Copernicus Open Access.
  Licensed under the Copernicus Data and Information Policy.
  https://sentinels.copernicus.eu/web/sentinel/terms-conditions

- **NISAR / ASF DAAC**: NASA / ISRO joint mission. Data available through
  NASA Earthdata: https://www.earthdata.nasa.gov/

- **MODIS (MOD16A2)**: NASA Land Processes Distributed Active Archive Center (LP DAAC).
  https://lpdaac.usgs.gov/

- **IMD Gridded Weather Data**: India Meteorological Department.
  https://www.imd.gov.in/

- **FAO-56 Penman-Monteith Formulation**: Food and Agriculture Organization of the
  United Nations. Allen, R.G. et al. (1998). Crop evapotranspiration — Guidelines for
  computing crop water requirements. FAO Irrigation and Drainage Paper 56.
  http://www.fao.org/3/X0490E/X0490E00.htm

- **SPEI (Log-Logistic Method)**: Vicente-Serrano, S.M., Beguería, S. & López-Moreno, J.I.
  (2010). A Multiscalar Drought Index Sensitive to Global Warming: The SPEI.
  Journal of Climate, 23(7), 1696–1718.

